  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhance scientific debate and policy advise on the slave trade, slavery and their legacies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Adressing painful memory and tragic history in order to build peaceful and inclusive societies requires that public policies be informed by scientific research and open debate on the issues ay stakes. 
Through its International Scientific Committee and the expertise developed since 1994, the UNESCO Slave Route Project will pursue its advise and support to Member States and other stakeholders to come to term with the memory, history and legacy of the slave trade and slavery by putting at their disposal the results of multidisciplinary research and recommandations based on sound research on ethical, political and sociocultural challenges and stakes of this tragedy and its cons&#xE9;quences in contemporary socieites.</narrative>
  </description>
